/* Headline "Adjust Dynamic ISF constant" */

/* Adjust Dynamic ISF constant */
"Individual adjustment of the computed dynamic ratios. Default is 0.5. The higher the value, the larger the correction of your ISF/CR will be for a high or a low blood glucose. Maximum/minumum correction is determined by the Autosens min/max settings.\n\nFor Sigmoid function an adjustment factor of 0.4 - 0.5 is recommended to begin with.\n\nFor the logaritmic formula there is less consensus, but starting around 0.8 is probably appropiate for most adult users. For younger users it's recommended to start even lower when using logaritmic formula, to avoid overly aggressive treatment." = "Individual adjustment of the computed dynamic ratios. Default is 0.5. The higher the value, the larger the correction of your ISF/CR will be for a high or a low blood glucose. Maximum/minumum correction is determined by the Autosens min/max settings.\n\nFor Sigmoid function an adjustment factor of 0.4 - 0.5 is recommended to begin with.\n\nFor the logaritmic formula there is less consensus, but starting around 0.8 is probably appropiate for most adult users. For younger users it's recommended to start even lower when using logaritmic formula, to avoid overly aggressive treatment.";

